  "prompt": "What are the true signs of Extroverts?",
  "response": "Here are some true signs of extroverts:\n\n1. Social Energy\n- Gain energy from being around people\n- Feel recharged after social interactions\n- Enjoy large gatherings and parties\n- Thrive in group settings\n\n2. Communication Traits\n- Talkative and outgoing\n- Comfortable starting conversations\n- Think out loud\n- Enjoy verbal processing\n- Prefer speaking to listening\n\n3. Social Behaviors\n- Have many friends and acquaintances\n- Easily make new connections\n- Prefer group activities\n- Comfortable with networking\n- Seek external stimulation\n\n4. Decision-Making\n- Prefer collaborative decision-making\n- Like brainstorming with others\n- Value external input\n- More spontaneous\n- Quick to take action\n\n5. Work Preferences\n- Enjoy teamwork\n- Prefer open office environments\n- Like interactive projects\n- Thrive in collaborative settings\n\n6. Emotional Characteristics\n- Expressive with emotions\n- Comfortable sharing feelings\n- Seek external validation\n- More impulsive\n- Quicker to show excitement\n\n7. Personal Interaction\n- Initiate social plans\n- Enjoy meeting new people\n- Less comfortable with long periods of solitude\n- Prefer active, engaging environments\n\nRemember, extroversion exists on a spectrum, and individuals may display these traits to varying degrees.",
